definition.def:
a characterization of the composition of a product;
This characterization may be a hierarchical representation where all assembly relationships are explicit or 
a partly implicit one, where some nodes are not related to a product but to a family of products with relationships conditioned by boolean expressions;
In the first approach, a part A would be specified as resulting from the assembly of a part B and a part C.
			The description of the product structure of products with a huge diversity, like vehicles proposed by major car manufacturers, is usually done using the second approach.

